                    </persName>)</author>
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/work/556</idno>
                <idno type="BHS">336</idno>
                <idno type="BHO">956</idno>
                <textLang mainLang="syr"/>
                <note type="abstract" source="#bib556-3 #bib556-10 #bib556-9">The Syriac text is a fragment that ends with 
                    <quote source="#bib556-10">The account about Peter the Iberian is finished.</quote> 
                It is disputed whether or not this is the remainder of a text from which the Georgian life of Peter the Iberian was translated 
                (see "Ancient Versions" below).</note>
                <note xml:lang="syr" type="explicit" source="#bib556-1">
                    <quote>ܘܗܢܐ ܐܣܪܐ ܕܫܬܩܐ ܡܠܐ ܙܒܢܐ ܢܣܒܘ̣. ܐܝܟܢܐ ܕܒܝܕ ܗܢܐ ܢܬܕܟܘܢ̣. ܘܢܐܠܦܘܢ ܐܝܟ ܕܓܪܝܓܪܝܘܣ ܐܡܿܪ. ܡܫܘܚܬܐ ܕܡܠܬܐ ܘܕܫܬܩܐ܀</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="fr" type="explicit" source="#bib556-1">
                    <quote>Et ils acceptèrent ce lien du silence temporaire pour grâce à lui se purifier et apprendre, comme dit Grégoire «la mesure de la parole et du silence».</quote>
                </note>
